<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-44',
    prompt: 'Schedule and complete a comprehensive review of your income tax situation with a qualified tax professional to address any outstanding tax obligations and understand post-bankruptcy filing requirements',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Tax obligations often survive bankruptcy and require immediate attention to prevent accumulating penalties and interest that could derail your recovery progress. A tax professional can help you understand which tax debts were discharged, set up payment plans for remaining obligations, and ensure you\'re properly positioned for future tax seasons. This consultation also provides guidance on claiming appropriate deductions and credits to maximize your refunds, which can accelerate your emergency fund building and debt repayment goals.'
  }</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-44',
    prompt: 'Schedule and complete a comprehensive review of your income tax situation with a qualified tax professional to address any outstanding tax obligations and understand post-bankruptcy filing requirements',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Tax obligations often survive bankruptcy and require immediate attention to prevent accumulating penalties and interest that could derail your recovery progress. A tax professional can help you understand which tax debts were discharged, set up payment plans for remaining obligations, and ensure you\'re properly positioned for future tax seasons. This consultation also provides guidance on claiming appropriate deductions and credits to maximize your refunds, which can accelerate your emergency fund building and debt repayment goals.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-45',
    prompt: 'Contact and interview 3 potential landlords to understand their rental criteria and obtain pre-approval letters for apartments within your budget',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Securing stable housing is fundamental to successful bankruptcy recovery, and pre-approval demonstrates your financial responsibility to property managers despite your bankruptcy history. Contact landlords directly to discuss your situation honestly, provide proof of income and references, and request written pre-approval for specific properties that fit your budget. This proactive approach helps you secure quality housing while building positive rental references that support future housing applications and demonstrates your commitment to financial stability.'
  }</parameter>
</invoke>
